{"expireTime":9007200904828481000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-ast-c468cd94edfda3a943b96a3c9cdd8489--","val":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"I spent a couple weekends looking into Kubernetes, and it looks to be start of a new project. So this post will outline the plans and requirements for the different modularized microservices that I will make as part of my project, in app.simonxu.com.","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":251,"offset":251},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":251,"offset":251},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Microservice 1: Database Display","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":2,"offset":254},"end":{"line":4,"column":34,"offset":286},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":253},"end":{"line":4,"column":35,"offset":287},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":"\nThe first one will be the most basic, it will update to show the contents of a firebase datastore including key-value pairs that are in my firebase database. This will update automatically ","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":35,"offset":287},"end":{"line":5,"column":190,"offset":477},"indent":[1]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":253},"end":{"line":5,"column":190,"offset":477},"indent":[1]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Microservice 2: REST API","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":2,"offset":480},"end":{"line":7,"column":26,"offset":504},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1,"offset":479},"end":{"line":7,"column":27,"offset":505},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":"\nThis will be some basic GET, POST, PUT, DELETE actions from REST based communication. I should be able to use the API I create to make requests vias Postman.","position":{"start"